      "role": "user",
      "content": "Thanks, that makes sense. We actually have a case where multiple modules need to reference the same Order object briefly before it's killed off, so `unique_ptr` might be too restrictive for certain parts of our pipeline. \n\nCan you show me how to refactor this using `std::shared_ptr` instead? I want to make sure we don't run into any issues with circular references or overhead that might slow down the execution loop.",
      "source": "evaluator"
